sentence.text: Further in vitro and in vivo results demonstrated that regulation of cell shape was associated with proliferation and metastasis of pancreatic cancer cells.

Mechanistically, the role of regulation of cell shape in pancreatic cancer might attribute to its regulation of c-Myc, HIF1Î± and NRF2 (Nuclear Factor, Erythroid 2-Like 2), which were key regulators of glycolysis and antioxidant response control.
